    "summary": "As professor in clinical developmental psychology and head of the section Clinical Developmental Psychology at the Vrije Universiteit Amsterdam I study and teach on the development, assessment and treatment of social functioning of individuals with and without psychopathology, in particular autism. I am keen to find new approaches to assess both how individuals with autism differ in their social functioning (both in positive and negative ways), and use these to assess treatment effects and innovate treatments. I co-founded the Netherlands Autism Register (NAR), www.nederlandsautismeregister.nl, a large longitudinal cohort of individuals with autism which is surveyed yearly. I strive for close collaboration with and individual dissemination of outcomes to affected individuals. These efforts are reflected in the teaching in our department. Within the Research Master Clinical and Developmental Psychopathology, we aim to translate fundamental research to clinical practice within the domain of psychopathology.",
